============================================================

Written to `tools/title-loop/docs/24-b15aa30/feedback.md`. Here's the summary:

**7 patterns across 18 failures (all generated):**

1. **OCR digit-for-letter in title, partial correction** (4) — title found but `1→l/i` not fully normalized; extractor returns corrupted title string
2. **OCR corruption annotation confuses extractor** (5) — `(OCR CORRUPTION: ...)` + `lngredients:` in body causes extractor to distrust/skip the first-line title, returning empty or a random body sentence
3. **Category/section header before title** (3) — `FISH & SEAFOOD`, `VEGETABLES`, or metadata bars push the real title to line 2+; extractor falls through to body text
4. **No title in captured text** (2) — OCR crop starts mid-recipe; extractor picks the next recipe's title or a random short phrase
5. **Compound title with `:` / `+` variation notation** (2) — full title on line 1 is split; only the variation half is returned (with `--` prefix)
6. **Polish title + English subtitle on line 2** (1) — short first line treated as ambiguous, subtitle skipped, body instruction returned
7. **Heavy body corruption with clean first-line title** (1) — pervasive corruption causes extractor to distrust even the clean title

**Highest real-file risk:** Patterns 3 (section headers), 4 (missing title), and 5 (compound/variation titles).
