{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Rk7Sq1U6zr36ym9EoVRgPQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me analyze the 18 failures and group them by root cause patterns.\n\nLooking at the failures:\n\n1. **OCR corruption - digit/letter substitution in title** (l→1, i→1, etc.):\n   - Beet Arugula Salad: \"BEET ARUGU1A SA1AD\" → extracted \"Beet Aruguia Saiad\" (tried to fix but failed partially)\n   - Blackberry Fool: \"B1ACKBERRY FOO1\" → extracted \"Biackberry Fooi\"\n   - Chleb Pszenny Razowy: \"CH1EB PSZENNY RAZOWY\" → extracted \"Chieb Pszenny Razowy\"\n   - Lemon Herb Grilled Chicken: \"LEMON HERB GRILÍED CHICKEN\" → extracted \"Lemon Herb Grilied Chicken\"\n\nThe extractor is catching the title but only partially correcting OCR artifacts—it handles some substitutions like 1→l but misses others, leaving corrupted characters in the output.\n\n2. **OCR corruption - title line present but extractor returns wrong content** (garbage tokens cause rejection):\n   - Braised Cod with White Wine: title \"Bra1sed Cod w1th Wh1te W1ne\" → extracted \"\" (empty)\n   - Drożdże Sernik: title \"Drożdże Sern1k\" → extracted \"Podaw4ć letni lub chłodny.\" (serving instruction instead)\n   - Piernik z Śliwkami: \"P1ern1k z Śliwkami\" → extracted \"Podaw4ć ciepło ze śmietaną lub lodami.\" (also grabbed serving text)\n   - Roasted Beet and Walnut Dip: \"Roasted Beet and Walnut D1p\" → extracted \"\" (empty)\n   - Żurek Krakowski: title present but extracted \"XxYyZz salt and pepper\" (complete garbage)\n\nThe pattern is becoming clearer—when these files have the OCR corruption marker right after the title and \"lngredients:\" with a lowercase L, the extractor gets thrown off and either returns nothing or pulls the wrong section entirely.\n\nLooking at another pattern where category headers appear before the actual recipe title, like \"FISH & SEAFOOD\" before \"Halibut with Saffron Cream Sauce\" or \"VEGETABLES\" before \"Roasted Asparagus with Parmesan,\" the extractor is grabbing content from the recipe body instead of the title. It seems to be treating the category line as the title and then pulling whatever comes next in the instructions or description.\n\nThere's also the issue of OCR cutting off mid-recipe, so files like Mushroom Risotto start with cooking instructions rather than a title, causing the extractor to either grab the next recipe's title or pull random ingredient names. And when recipes are listed with variations separated by colons or plus signs, the extractor isn't handling those compound titles correctly. The extractor is also getting confused when there's both a Polish title and English subtitle on separate lines, sometimes pulling content from deeper in the recipe instead. Looking at cases like Placki Ziemniaczane, where the title is clearly on the first line but the extracted text contains OCR corruption, I'm seeing a pattern emerge: there are about four recipes where the title has digit-for-letter corruption (like 1 instead of l or i) that the extractor partially catches but doesn't fully correct—Beet Arugula Salad, Blackberry Fool, Chleb Pszenny Razowy, and Lemon Herb Grilled Chicken all fall into this category.\n\nThen there's a second group of five recipes where an OCR corruption marker appears on line 3 followed by \"Ingredients,\" and this annotation seems to throw off the extractor entirely, causing it to either skip the title or grab a random body line instead. A third pattern shows up in three recipes where a category or section header sits before the actual recipe title, confusing the extraction order.\n\nI'm also seeing cases where the title is completely missing from the start of the content—either the recipe jumps straight into instructions or ingredients—and Placki Ziemniaczane is borderline here since the title exists but the body is heavily corrupted. Then there are compound titles where two recipes are listed together with a colon or plus sign, but the extractor only picks up the variation marker instead of the full title. Finally, one recipe has a Polish title with an English subtitle on line 2, and the extractor grabs a body instruction instead of recognizing the actual title.\n\nNow I'm ready to write the feedback.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":24042,"cache_read_input_tokens":10352,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":24042},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"27d63b2a-9f23-428b-bc7f-4437a6d41dd0","uuid":"7805c41c-33e0-484c-9f67-44f7dd1a1cb9"}
